headline: Adyen sets new targets, outpacing European rivals
summary: (Reuters) -Adyen, the Dutch company known for handling payment processing for eBay and Spotify, set ​new financial targets on Tuesday, aiming for stronger profitability and steady ‌revenue growth.  The company is gaining ground against U.S. rivals despite most European peers struggling,‌ helped by its strategy of expanding in North America and Asia.  Following 2026, annual revenue growth is expected to come ‍in at around 20% "in any given year," Adyen said, adding that it will refine its outlook each February.

headline: Meg Whitman on Leading Through Change | WSJ Leadership Institute
summary: The former eBay chief executive reflects on how tariffs and trade tensions have reverberated across global markets, and how boards can successfully navigate rapid technological change while staying innovative and compliant.
